---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy" description="Privacy policy for ilo.">
  <main class="site-frame flex-1 space-y-8 pt-10 pb-12">
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="text-foreground-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-6 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Local software</h2>
        <p>The ilo CLI stores drafts and schedules on your machine. X OAuth tokens and client secrets are stored in your operating system keychain. They are not sent to ilo.so.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Website analytics</h2>
        <p>ilo.so uses Clicky to measure aggregate website traffic and understand which public pages and tools are useful. The site has no ilo accounts or authentication cookies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Public tools</h2>
        <p>When you use a hosted tool, ilo.so receives the inputs needed to complete that request, such as a public URL, handle, or search query. Do not submit secrets or private data to public tool endpoints.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Third-party services</h2>
        <p>The local CLI talks directly to X when you connect an account or publish. Hosted tools may contact public X, Bluesky, and webpage endpoints to return the requested result.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Self-hosting</h2>
        <p>If you deploy a fork, that deployment is controlled by its operator. Check their policy and source before sending data to it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
